    "body": "I was having a look into this.\r\n@jarradh do you mean something like this :\r\n```\r\nvar StatusHttpProvider = function (host, timeout) {\r\n    this.host = host || 'http://localhost:8545';\r\n    this.timeout = timeout || 0;\r\n    this.defaultHttpProvider = new web3.providers.HttpProvider(host, timeout);\r\n};\r\n\r\nStatusHttpProvider.prototype.send = function (payload) {\r\n    if (this.host.indexOf('https') == -1) {\r\n        return this.defaultHttpProvider.send(payload)\r\n    } else {\r\n        throw new Error('You tried to send \"'+ payload.method +'\" synchronously over HTTPS. Synchronous requests are only supported over HTTP, sorry.');\r\n    }\r\n};\r\n```\r\nOr you mean copying the code from the send method in the default httpprovider ?\r\nNot sure I understand correctly ...\r\n(Also I'm not saying this is a clean solution, it could be improved obviously, but it's more to see if it's what you mean ?)\r\n",
